stylometry: The project was on Wyatt Printing, and the problem was when to use each machine (Sakurai and Copier).  The Sakurai had a large fixed cost ($564) and the copier only $0.5, but the variable cost were 0 for the Sakurai and $0.006 (click charge) for the copier.  We decided to look at just one 8 hour shift and figure out what machine to use depending on the output needed.  Sakurai could produce 8000 pages an hour and copier 2100 an hour.  We found that though the copier is going to be much cheaper for the smaller projects (up to about 70000) the output was not enough to do what we needed in that 8 hr shift.  In conclusion, if you wanted to get it all done in the one day not worried about cost, you are going to use the Sakurai, but if you are looking for the lowest cost and have the time you are going to use the copier up to about 70,000 pages.  The copier is slower but cheaper.
